whyCorpcareCard.cardDescription: We offer competitive interest rates on our fixed deposits, helping our clients earn more on their investment and grow their wealth over time.
We offer a range of options, such as short-term and long-term deposits, allowing our clients to choose the term that best fits their needs and financial goals.

disclosure.disclosureHeading: Can Company/Trust/LLPs/Partnership Firms/HUFs invest in a recurring deposit scheme?
disclosure.disclosureDescription: Only individuals can invest in a recurring deposit scheme.

disclosure.disclosureHeading: What is the lock in period for premature withdrawal?
disclosure.disclosureDescription: The fixed deposit should complete at least up to 3 months.

disclosure.disclosureHeading: What are the interest rates applicable after 3 months – before/ up to 6 months?
disclosure.disclosureDescription: The interest rate range applicable for individual category ranges from No Interest applicable up to 4% and for non- individual category No interest is applicable.

disclosure.disclosureHeading: What are the interest rates applicable after 6 months – before / up to maturity?
disclosure.disclosureDescription: The interest rate applicable for individual and non-individual category ranges from 1% up to 3%.

disclosure.disclosureHeading: What are the interest rates applicable if no rate is specified for the period for which deposit is issued?
disclosure.disclosureDescription: The interest rate applicable for individual and non-individual category ranges from 2% up to 3%.

disclosure.disclosureHeading: What is the rate of interest on Loan against Fixed Deposit?
disclosure.disclosureDescription: The rate of interest applicable on Loan against Fixed Deposit is 2% more than the effective FD rate of interest.

disclosure.disclosureHeading: What is the maximum loan amount that can be availed?
disclosure.disclosureDescription: You can avail loan amount up to 75% of the fixed deposit amount.

disclosure.disclosureHeading: Is CIBIL score checked as a part of processing of loan?
disclosure.disclosureDescription: No, the CIBIL score is not checked the loan is given on the basis of existing Fixed Deposit.

disclosure.disclosureHeading: What is the eligibility for applying Loan against FD request?
disclosure.disclosureDescription: Loan can be taken against FD after completion of 90 days from the effective date of deposit.

disclosure.disclosureHeading: What are the mandatory KYC documents required for generating Corporate Fixed Deposits?
disclosure.disclosureDescription: COI, REGISTRATION CERTIFICATE, MOA & AOA, PAN, RESOLUTION FROM BOD
